{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"05ea42da-9e27-47b3-ad96-39c1a941f937","content":"Package added. **2. Run tests with the hang timeout:**\n\n```\ndotnet test -- --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nThis will:\n- Monitor all tests for hangs\n- If any test (or the overall run) stalls for **5 minutes**, it creates a **hang dump** (process dump) and terminates the run\n- The dump file lets you inspect thread stacks to find the deadlock/hang\n\nYou can also specify where to save the dump:\n\n```\ndotnet test -- --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m --hangdump-directory ./hang-dumps\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ab07e82c-b791-4771-a9ef-5f4cf6d0c8b6","outputTokens":143},"id":"0a66cdc3-f159-439c-8709-f4278f921d5e","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:21:41.857Z","parentId":"9cff2253-49f9-4d67-bb94-c776413483f2"}
